 (noise).","bounding":[873.2179565429688,38.862422943115234,415.44183349609375,281.1590576171875],"color":"#3f789e","font_size":24,"flags":{},"description":"Blurring smooths out the asphalt so Canny doesn't detect every pebble as an edge."},{"id":3,"title":"Apply Canny Edge Detection","bounding":[1312.19091796875,44.287811279296875,377.1600036621094,276.02001953125],"color":"#3f789e","font_size":24,"flags":{},"description":"Pixels with gradients above 150 are definitely edges.\nPixels between 50 and 150 are kept only if they connect to a definite edge."}],"config":{},"extra":{"filemeta":{"name":"Canny Edge Pipeline for Lane Detection","description":"This graph demonstrates a foundational computer vision pipeline for Advanced Driver Assistance Systems (ADAS), specifically focusing on lane detection using Canny edge detection.","tags":["Lane Detection","Edge Detection","ADAS"]},"ds":{"scale":0.6830134553650705,"offset":[1120.5745909090924,394.2777748579542]}},"version":0.4,"uuid":"64da1913-338c-48f9-a210-e67f60c6fc5e"}